AGI -&nbsp;Involved in case for the death of Andrea Prospero, the young man found lifeless on 29 January. This morning an order of precaution to domiciles from the mobile team of Perugia was carried out against a young 18-year-old boy from the province of Rome. The investigation is challenged by the crime of instigation or aid to suicide. As reported by Chief Prosecutor Raffaele Cantone, the two would have known virtually in the chat. In the conversations recovered by the postal police, Prospero would have expressed several times the will to take away life and the interlocutor, according to the report again, would have incited it to end.
<br
<br Among the chats also those immediately prior to taking drugs that caused their death. Even in the face of the expulsion of the student of Abruzzo, the interlocutor, instead of convincing him to desist he would also provide indications on how to take the drugs, advising him, Cantone reported, also to ingest the drugs with wine. In conversations also the motivations that would lead Andrea Prospero to kill himself, "regions that hold the personal sphere" explained the Canton Attorney.
<br> &nbsp;
<h2> A second survey There's also a second investigator. &nbsp;It would be a young bell, accused of providing the substances assumed by Andrea Prospero. To him, the investigators arrived from the analysis of the chats of a well-known social. The two investigators, said the prosecutor Raffaele Cantone, would not be connected. Both knowledge would go back to the common attendance of a chat. At the home of the young bell, the investigators found about 10 thousand euros in cash, which are attributed to the illicit market.
<br> &nbsp;
<h2> Who was Andrea Prospero</h2> Andrea Prospero from Lanciano, in the province of Chieti, was a university student outside, enrolled in the course of Computer Science of the University of Perugia, where he studied together with his sister Anna: she was the one who alarmed the disappearance when his brother had not responded to his calls. After his death, 5 phones and 60&nbsp were found;schede sim traceable to the boy, who had suggested involvement in some computer scam. However, the acquaintances, in several TV broadcasts described it as a “non-silent” student, which from the very beginning has led to a role as victim of Andrea, than a crook.&nbsp;
<br
<br> "We are faced with a story that moves in the virtual reality that unfortunately brought its effects into reality. The investigations were made possible thanks to the analysis of computer equipment, without which it would have been more complicated to reach the results of today". It has emphasized the Deputy prosecutor of Perugia, Giuseppe Petrazzini, illustrating the results of the investigation.&nbsp;
<br> "Virtual reality involves people without ever meeting, with a danger to public security and personal security," he added.
<br> &nbsp;
<h2 Prospero family lawyer: “welcome our idea”</h2> The precautionary measure against an investigation for the hypothesis of instigation or aid to suicide, "it seems to confirm what we have always supported" comments lawyer Francesco Mangano who with his colleague Carlo Pacelli assists the family of the young Lanciano. As already in the past considered by the family, Andrea would have been crushed by a situation bigger than him from which he would not find a way out.&nbsp;
<br
<br> &nbsp;"It is an unspeakable and inenarratable pain that of the family who is now reverted and thought is directed towards other lids. Let's thank the investigators for the activity." So lawyer Pacelli. "The investigation goes on there are circumstances to be clarified as the Prosecutor of the Republic began to give answers to the family. In the necessary time the other dark circumstances will also be revealed. Even in order to ensure that Andrea's sad fate, a terrible consolation, can be a warning for many other boys who on the net do not find the ocean where to navigate but rather a deep and extremely dangerous abyss," added Mangano.
<h2 Sister Anna: "He left an unknowing vacuum"</h2> &nbsp;"The vacuum he left Andrea is unknowing. We trust in justice and thank the inquirents, lawyers and all the people who helped bring out the truth and who will help us." So Anna Prospero, sister of Andrea.&nbsp;
